[1] Ghana (Tamale), positive environmental sample, PV2 - media report
Date: Thu 11 Jul 2019
Source: Business Ghana [edited]
http://www.businessghana.com/site/news/general/191347/Public-Health-Emergency:-Polio-virus-type-2-detected-in-Tamale-MoH


The Ministry of Health (MoH) says it has detected polio virus type 2 in the environment in Tamale in the Northern region of Ghana, which constitutes a public health emergency. Consequently, the ministry has detailed field investigations to identify a possible source of infection and determine the extent of geographic spread.

In a statement signed and issued by the chief director of the ministry on [Wed 10 Jul 2019], the MoH explained that the virus was detected through a routine surveillance in collaboration with the Ghana Health Service (GHS) and confirmed by the Noguchi Memorial Institute of Medical and Research Centre (NMIMR).

This, the ministry said, constitutes a public health emergency.

[A copy of the statement issued by the MoH on the public health emergency can be found at the source URL.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to another media report, "The type 2 strain of the polio virus was confirmed earlier this week by the Noguchi Memorial Institute for Medical Research (NMIMR) to be similar to the type that broke out in Nigeria recently" (https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/polio-resurfaces-in-tamale.html).

If confirmed to be genetically related to one of the cVDPV2s currently circulating in Nigeria, this will be further "evidence" of the widespread reach of the cVDPV outbreaks in Nigeria and the impact on other countries in Africa (and potentially outside of Africa) as seen back in 2004.

Tamale is located in the Northern region of Ghana, not sharing international borders with other countries. A map of Ghana showing administrative divisions can be found at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/ghana_map.htm.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Ghana: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6564898,53. - Mod.MPP]

