[The above article is an excellent discussion on what has been going on. Unfortunately, I am not as confident that the WPV1 is no longer circulating in Africa. There are still areas in northern Nigeria with extreme civil unrest, and where there exist pockets of unvaccinated individuals. In 2016, there was an outbreak of WPV1 identified in Borno state, with a virus that was genetically related to a virus that was last identified as circulating in 2011. Interpretation: a below-the-radarscope circulation of the WPV1 continued in the northern state of Nigeria. Further confirmation of the existing pockets of susceptibles in northern Nigeria is currently seen by the multiple outbreaks of cVDPV2 in Nigeria, a sign of pockets of susceptibles.

And the number of countries with documented circulation of VDPVs continues to grow this year (2019), signaling the impact of decreasing vaccination coverages in multiple countries. When we 1st launched the polio eradication effort in the Americas region in 1985, it was a simpler time, with warring factions that put down their arms to permit national and subnational vaccination campaigns to interrupt transmission of the WPV in their countries, with the last case of WPV confirmed in 1991 in Peru. The world political scene has markedly changed since then, and children's health is now being held hostage to political gains: a very sorry state of affairs. In addition, there has been an explosion of anti-vaccination information using social media, so that areas without civil unrest are refusing vaccinations of children based on erroneous information, adding to the sorry state of affairs. - Mod.MPP]
